description._content: Description: A view of part of the terrace of "Ao-n te Tarine" on the north coast of Ocean Island. These terraces were built on the coral pinnacles by the natives before the coming of the white man and are of considerable anthropological interest. Location: Ocean Island, Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Description: Te Toa, the clan meeting house of Buakonikai village, Ocean Island. Location: Ocean Island, Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/642. This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons.
